result.description: A bait ball, or baitball, occurs when small fish swarm in a tightly packed spherical formation about a common centre.
Object found on the lake bottom.

An imaginary line on the lake bottom created from a sudden increase or decrease in depth; An abrupt contrast in the underwater conditions(i.e.: weedline, thermocline, shadeline, water color change, etc.).
The submerged riverbed; A type of structure used by fish during migration.
A stream of water moving continuously in a certain direction.
30 ft. deep or deeper; the deepest water in the immediate area, usually the channel.
A breakline or structure where there is a sudden drop into the deepest water.
A submerged gulch, creek, or wash that feeds into the main channel; Structure that fish use during their migration from deep water to shallow water.
An area of shallow water with a relatively even bottom
An accumulations of foam, with trapped insects, exuvia, etc. found on the surface of freshwater water courses or bodies.
An underwater island; A structure in which the lake bottom rises up from the surrounding area.

in a lake: A type of underwater structure in which the shallow water protrudes out into the lake more than the surrounding area; In a river: depositional feature made of alluvium that accumulates on the inside bend of streams and rivers below the slip-off slope
A type of structure where a long narrow hump exists along the sides of a channel or feeder creek; A levee.
Large rocks placed by man along the sides of dams and roadways to prevent erosion
A type of structure in which the bottom is covered by rock and rubble; A potential food source if found shallow.
A type of structure which is formed from two inside bends facing opposite directions.
An area containing shallow water.
An area void of structure, which contains very little shallow water due to steep shoreline, drop off conditions.
A horizontal plane of rapidly changing water temperature.
Structure type that doesn't fit into any of the available types

rocks or boulders grouped together
spaces without weeds in weed beds
